**Result:** `{&quot;birthDate&quot;:&quot;2015-03-01&quot;}`

&gt;`curl -v -POST -H &quot;Content-Type:application/json&quot; -d &quot;{\&quot;birthDate\&quot;:\&quot;2015-03-01\&quot;}&quot; http://localhost:8080/api/person`&lt;br/&gt;
**Result:** `2015-03-01`

-----

See also [**here**](https://stackoverflow.com/a/27772267/2587435) for JAXB solution.


### UPDATE

The `JSR310Module` is deprecated as of version 2.7 of Jackson. Instead, you should register the module `JavaTimeModule`. It is still the same dependency.

