answers.body_markdown:
Use [Stream::map][1] to transform each line and [Stream::collect][2] to create a new list from the stream.

Replacement for your code would be:

    List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; res = lines.stream()
      .map(line -&gt; {
        List&lt;String&gt; aux = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        for (String element : line.split(&quot;,&quot;)) {
          aux.add(element);
        }
        return aux;
      })
      .collect(Collectors.toList());

But we can simplify it by using [Arrays::asList][3] to create `List&lt;String&gt;` from `String[]` without writing the for loop.

    List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; res = lines.stream()
      .map(line -&gt; Arrays.asList(line.split(&quot;,&quot;)))
      .collect(Collectors.toList());


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/stream/Stream.html#map-java.util.function.Function-
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/stream/Stream.html#collect-java.util.stream.Collector-
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Arrays.html#asList-T...-

